headline: Exclusive-Activist investor Ananym Capital pushes for changes at Henry Schein, sources say
summary: NEW YORK (Reuters) -Activist investor Ananym Capital Management is urging healthcare products distributor Henry Schein to refresh its board, cut costs, tackle succession planning and consider selling its medical distribution business, sources close to matter said on Monday.  A sale of the medical distribution business could help drive up the share price by roughly 20%, while earnings per share could jump by some 35% if spending were curtailed, Ananym has told Schein executives, according to the sources.  Henry Schein shares closed up 7.5% at $73.89 on Monday.
